      "comment": "THAI TIGER (1) lines up chasing another win after scoring over 450m at Shepparton in 25.52, set up by a fast early sectional. Recorded one of the quickest times on the card in scoring last start. The one to beat again. HOLLYWOOD FRANKY (8) failed to come into contention last start after drifting back at this track, but prior to that won by one length at Shepparton (22.16) beating Solitary Flicker in a Special conditions Veteran race on February 16. Consistent performer from this draw with a win and three minor placings to his credit. Great chance to atone. SIR DODGE (7) has been beaten for early speed lately, last time finishing fifth (38.06) in a Special conditions race at Angle Park. Solid record at the distance winning three races. The form out of last race has been strong. Better than the latest run and deserves another chance. GO BOY (4) must be respected at his pet distance.",
